    "summary": "I am a teacher and have been a software professional for over 15 years with work experience in both technical and non-technical projects. \n\nI contributed to projects related to website development, 2D\\3D graphics, medical applications and advanced machine control. I worked for many years in multi disciplinary teams with a strong international focus and multi site development involved.\n\nI have excellent knowledge with years of practical experience in the complete software engineering cycle: requirements elicitation, sw & test design, architecture, implementation, managing (release) planning, scrum master,  software process improvements, usabillity analysis. One of my strong points is that I easily can understand both technical and business needs of a software project and switch between them.\n\nWhat drives me is helping & sharing knowledge in any way. Creativity. Actively looking for & implementing Improvements on personal, team & process level.\n\nSince my first experience with programming on the age of 10, I have been working with numerous programming languages. My main coding expertise is in C\\C++ and Object Oriented Design, with also a good C# and Java foundation. \n\nI like software projects which are very close to user interfaces. This gives the possibility to explore other fields I am interested in, like human perception & user experience when people are involved in computer interaction. I believe Software engineering is more than just a technical business.\n\nSpecialties: Sharing knowledge, Agile, Scrum, Software engineering processes, Object Oriented Design, Design Patterns, UI usability, Software Testing, TDD, Windows platform, Multi-Threaded programming & design, 3D, global mindset",
